{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CVpbK2TRDDi3Muo1NEVzyb","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 6.3: Evaluator Prompt Template\n2\t\n3\tStatus: review\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a developer,\n8\tI want the evaluator agent YAML to include anti-leniency instructions and a structured prompt template,\n9\tso that the evaluator requires evidence for every verdict and produces reliable, schema-compliant JSON output.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** `templates/agents/evaluator.yaml` exists\n14\t   **When** inspected\n15\t   **Then** it contains a `prompt_template` field with a multi-line string instructing the evaluator to: read ACs from `./story-files/`, independently determine how to test each AC, require evidence (commands run + output captured) for every PASS, score UNKNOWN if unable to verify, never give benefit of the doubt, and re-verify from scratch (no caching of prior results)\n16\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n17\t\n18\t2. **Given** the evaluator prompt template in `evaluator.yaml`\n19\t   **When** inspected\n20\t   **Then** it includes explicit anti-leniency instructions: \"Assume code is broken until demonstrated otherwise\", \"Never give benefit of the doubt\", \"Every PASS requires commands_run evidence — if you cannot run a command to verify, score UNKNOWN\"\n21\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t3. **Given** the evaluator prompt template\n24\t   **When** inspected\n25\t   **Then** it instructs the evaluator to output a JSON object matching the `EvaluatorVerdict` schema defined in `src/schemas/verdict.schema.json` — including `verdict`, `score`, `findings` array with per-AC `status`, `evidence.commands_run`, `evidence.output_observed`, and `evidence.reasoning`\n26\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n27\t\n28\t4. **Given** the evaluator prompt template\n29\t   **When** inspected\n30\t   **Then** it instructs the evaluator that it has access to Docker (`docker exec`, `docker logs`, `docker ps`) and observability query endpoints, but NOT to source code — and it must use these tools to gather evidence\n31\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t5. **Given** the `ResolvedAgent` interface in `agent-resolver.ts`\n34\t   **When** `evaluator.yaml` is loaded via `resolveAgent('evaluator')`\n35\t   **Then** the resolved agent includes the `prompt_template` field value from the YAML\n36\t   **And** `compileSubagentDefinition()` incorporates the `prompt_template` into the compiled `instructions` string\n37\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n38\t\n39\t6. **Given** `compileSubagentDefinition()` in `agent-resolver.ts`\n40\t   **When** a `ResolvedAgent` has a `prompt_template` field\n41\t   **Then** the `prompt_template` content is appended to the `instructions` string in the compiled `SubagentDefinition`\n42\t   **And** when no `prompt_template` is present, the compiled output is unchanged from the current behavior\n43\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n44\t\n45\t7. **Given** the `EVALUATOR_PROMPT` constant in `evaluator.ts`\n46\t   **When** `runEvaluator()` dispatches the evaluator\n47\t   **Then** the prompt passed to `dispatchAgent()` is replaced with a call that uses the prompt template from the compiled `SubagentDefinition.instructions` (or a dedicated prompt builder function) instead of the hardcoded one-liner\n48\t   **And** the prompt includes the story file paths and verdict output path (`./verdict/`)\n49\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n50\t\n51\t8. **Given** `agent.schema.json` in `src/schemas/`\n52\t   **When** inspected\n53\t   **Then** it allows an optional `prompt_template` field of type `string` on agent definitions\n54\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n55\t\n56\t9. **Given** unit tests for the prompt template integration\n57\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n58\t   **Then** tests pass at 80%+ coverage for the changed code covering: evaluator.yaml loads with prompt_template, compileSubagentDefinition includes prompt_template in instructions, evaluator dispatch uses the structured prompt, prompt contains anti-leniency keywords, prompt references verdict JSON schema structure\n59\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n60\t\n61\t10. **Given** `npm run build` is executed\n62\t    **When** the build completes\n63\t    **Then** it succeeds with zero errors\n64\t    **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n65\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n66\t\n67\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n68\t\n69\t- [x] Task 1: Update agent JSON schema to allow prompt_template (AC: #8)\n70\t  - [x] Add optional `prompt_template` field (type: string) to `src/schemas/agent.schema.json`\n71\t  - [x] Verify existing agent YAMLs still validate\n72\t\n73\t- [x] Task 2: Update ResolvedAgent interface and compileSubagentDefinition (AC: #5, #6)\n74\t  - [x] Add optional `prompt_template?: string` to `ResolvedAgent` interface in `agent-resolver.ts`\n75\t  - [x] In `compileSubagentDefinition()`, append `prompt_template` content to `instructions` after `prompt_patches`\n76\t  - [x] Ensure backward compatibility: agents without `prompt_template` produce identical output\n77\t\n78\t- [x] Task 3: Write the evaluator prompt template in evaluator.yaml (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4)\n79\t  - [x] Add `prompt_template` field to `templates/agents/evaluator.yaml` with structured multi-line prompt\n80\t  - [x] Include anti-leniency instructions: assume broken, no benefit of doubt, UNKNOWN if can't verify\n81\t  - [x] Include verdict JSON schema structure reference (verdict, score, findings array)\n82\t  - [x] Include tool access instructions: Docker commands available, observability endpoints available, no source code\n83\t  - [x] Include output instructions: write JSON to `./verdict/` directory, one finding per AC\n84\t\n85\t- [x] Task 4: Update evaluator.ts to use prompt template (AC: #7)\n86\t  - [x] Remove or deprecate the hardcoded `EVALUATOR_PROMPT` constant\n87\t  - [x] Build the dispatch prompt from the evaluator's compiled instructions and story file context\n88\t  - [x] Ensure the prompt includes story file paths available in `./story-files/`\n89\t  - [x] Ensure the prompt references `./verdict/` as the output directory\n90\t\n91\t- [x] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: #9, #10)\n92\t  - [x] Test: `evaluator.yaml` resolves with `prompt_template` field present\n93\t  - [x] Test: `compileSubagentDefinition()` includes `prompt_template` in instructions when present\n94\t  - [x] Test: `compileSubagentDefinition()` output unchanged when `prompt_template` absent\n95\t  - [x] Test: evaluator dispatch prompt contains anti-leniency keywords (\"broken\", \"benefit of the doubt\", \"UNKNOWN\")\n96\t  - [x] Test: evaluator dispatch prompt references verdict JSON structure\n97\t  - [x] Test: evaluator dispatch prompt includes story file paths\n98\t  - [x] Test: `agent.schema.json` accepts agent config with `prompt_template`\n99\t  - [x] Test: `agent.schema.json` accepts agent config without `prompt_template`\n100\t  - [x] Test: existing agent-resolver tests pass without regression\n101\t  - [x] Test: existing evaluator tests pass without regression\n102\t  - [x] Verify `npm run build` succeeds with zero errors\n103\t  - [x] Verify 80%+ coverage on changed files\n104\t\n105\t## Dev Notes\n106\t\n107\t### Module Design\n108\t\n109\tThis story bridges two existing modules:\n110\t1. **evaluator.yaml** (agent template) — gains a `prompt_template` with structured anti-leniency instructions\n111\t2. **agent-resolver.ts** — gains `prompt_template` support in `ResolvedAgent` and `compileSubagentDefinition()`\n112\t3. **evaluator.ts** — replaces the hardcoded one-liner prompt with one built from the compiled agent instructions\n113\t\n114\tThe prompt template is stored in the agent YAML (not hardcoded in TypeScript) so that users can patch it via the `extends` mechanism. This is consistent with how `prompt_patches.append` already works, but `prompt_template` provides the full base prompt rather than an append-only patch.\n115\t\n116\t### Integration Points\n117\t\n118\t- `templates/agents/evaluator.yaml` — the evaluator agent definition (add `prompt_template`)\n119\t- `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` — agent JSON schema (add optional `prompt_template`)\n120\t- `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` — `ResolvedAgent` interface and `compileSubagentDefinition()` function\n121\t- `src/lib/evaluator.ts` — `EVALUATOR_PROMPT` constant and `runEvaluator()` dispatch call\n122\t- `src/schemas/verdict.schema.json` — referenced in prompt template (not modified)\n123\t- `src/lib/verdict-parser.ts` — downstream consumer of evaluator output (not modified)\n124\t\n125\t### Data Flow\n126\t\n127\t```\n128\tevaluator.yaml (with prompt_template)\n129\t  → resolveAgent('evaluator') → ResolvedAgent (with prompt_template)\n130\t  → compileSubagentDefinition(resolved) → SubagentDefinition (instructions include prompt_template)\n131\t  → runEvaluator(options) → dispatchAgent(definition, prompt, options)\n132\t  → evaluator agent executes in isolated workspace\n133\t  → reads ./story-files/, runs Docker commands, writes JSON verdict\n134\t  → parseVerdict(output) → EvaluatorVerdict (story 6-2, unchanged)\n135\t```\n136\t\n137\t### Prompt Template Content (Draft)\n138\t\n139\tThe prompt template should include these sections:\n140\t\n141\t1. **Role context** — \"You are verifying acceptance criteria for a software story\"\n142\t2. **Input** — \"Read acceptance criteria from ./story-files/. Each file contains the ACs to verify.\"\n143\t3. **Anti-leniency rules** — \"Assume the code is broken until proven otherwise. Never give benefit of the doubt. If you cannot run a command to verify an AC, score it UNKNOWN — never PASS without evidence.\"\n144\t4. **Tool access** — \"You have access to Docker (docker exec, docker logs, docker ps) and observability query endpoints. You do NOT have access to source code.\"\n145\t5. **Evidence requirements** — \"Every PASS verdict MUST include: commands_run (the exact commands you ran), output_observed (the actual terminal output), and reasoning (why this proves the AC passes).\"\n146\t6. **Output format** — \"Output a single JSON object matching this structure: { verdict: 'pass'|'fail', score: { passed, failed, unknown, total }, findings: [{ ac, description, status, evidence: { commands_run, output_observed, reasoning } }] }\"\n147\t7. **Output location** — \"Write your verdict JSON to ./verdict/\"\n148\t8. **Re-verification** — \"Re-verify everything from scratch. Do not assume prior results. Do not cache.\"\n149\t\n150\t### Existing EVALUATOR_PROMPT\n151\t\n152\tThe current hardcoded prompt in `evaluator.ts` (line 47-48):\n153\t```typescript\n154\tconst EVALUATOR_PROMPT =\n155\t  'Read the acceptance criteria in ./story-files/. For each AC, determine if it passes by running commands and checking output. Report your findings as JSON.';\n156\t```\n157\t\n158\tThis is intentionally minimal (per story 6-1 dev notes: \"The full prompt template with anti-leniency instructions and structured output enforcement is story 6-3\"). This story replaces it with the full template.\n159\t\n160\t### prompt_template vs prompt_patches\n161\t\n162\t- `prompt_patches.append` — additional instructions appended to the compiled instructions (existing mechanism)\n163\t- `prompt_template` — the full base prompt for what the agent should DO when dispatched (new field)\n164\t\n165\tThese are different concerns:\n166\t- `instructions` = who you are (identity, principles, communication style) + patches\n167\t- `prompt_template` = what you should do (task-specific instructions)\n168\t\n169\tIn `compileSubagentDefinition()`, the order should be:\n170\t1. Identity and persona (existing)\n171\t2. Principles (existing)\n172\t3. prompt_patches.append (existing)\n173\t4. prompt_template (new — appended last as the task instructions)\n174\t\n175\t### Schema Change\n176\t\n177\t`agent.schema.json` needs:\n178\t```json\n179\t\"prompt_template\": {\n180\t  \"type\": \"string\",\n181\t  \"description\": \"Task-specific prompt template included in compiled instructions\"\n182\t}\n183\t```\n184\t\n185\t### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n186\t\n187\t- **Do NOT hardcode the prompt in evaluator.ts** — it lives in evaluator.yaml so users can patch it\n188\t- **Do NOT modify verdict-parser.ts** — prompt template affects input, not output parsing\n189\t- **Do NOT modify workflow-engine.ts** — prompt construction happens before the engine dispatches\n190\t- **Do NOT add runtime template variable substitution** (e.g., `{{story_key}}`) — the prompt template is a static string included in instructions; dynamic context (story files, trace ID) is provided via the dispatch prompt argument\n191\t- **Do NOT change the EvaluatorVerdict schema** — the prompt references it, doesn't modify it\n192\t- **Do NOT remove `disallowedTools` from evaluator.yaml** — the prompt template is additive\n193\t\n194\t### Project Structure Notes\n195\t\n196\t- Modified file: `templates/agents/evaluator.yaml` — add `prompt_template` field\n197\t- Modified file: `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` — add optional `prompt_template` property\n198\t- Modified file: `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` — add `prompt_template` to `ResolvedAgent`, update `compileSubagentDefinition()`\n199\t- Modified file: `src/lib/evaluator.ts` — replace hardcoded `EVALUATOR_PROMPT` with prompt from compiled definition\n200\t- Modified test file: `src/lib/__tests__/agent-resolver.test.ts` — add prompt_template tests\n201\t- Modified test file: `src/lib/__tests__/evaluator.test.ts` — update prompt assertions\n202\t- No new files expected\n203\t\n204\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n205\t\n206\tFrom story 6-1 (evaluator module):\n207\t- `EVALUATOR_PROMPT` is a simple one-liner at line 47-48 of `evaluator.ts`\n208\t- `runEvaluator()` passes `EVALUATOR_PROMPT` to `dispatchAgent()` at line 128-132\n209\t- `buildUnknownOutput()` generates fallback JSON matching EvaluatorVerdict shape — the prompt template must reference this same shape\n210\t- The evaluator agent definition is passed in via `options.agentDefinition` (pre-compiled `SubagentDefinition`)\n211\t\n212\tFrom story 6-2 (verdict schema & parsing):\n213\t- `verdict.schema.json` defines the exact JSON structure the prompt must instruct the evaluator to produce\n214\t- `parseVerdict()` enforces PASS-evidence invariant — the prompt should tell the evaluator to always include evidence to avoid downgrades\n215\t- `VerdictParseError` with retry semantics means the prompt should emphasize outputting valid JSON\n216\t\n217\tFrom story 3-2 (embedded agent templates):\n218\t- `resolveAgent()` loads YAML from `templates/agents/`, applies patches, returns `ResolvedAgent`\n219\t- `compileSubagentDefinition()` converts `ResolvedAgent` to `SubagentDefinition` with `instructions` string\n220\t- Agent YAML schema validated by `agent.schema.json` — new fields must be added there\n221\t\n222\tFrom story 3-3 (agent resolver):\n223\t- `resolveAgent()` → `loadAgentFile()` → `applyAgentPatch()` → `ResolvedAgent`\n224\t- `prompt_patches.append` is applied in `compileSubagentDefinition()` at line 339-341\n225\t- New `prompt_template` follows the same pattern but is a separate field\n226\t\n227\t### References\n228\t\n229\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 6.3: Evaluator Prompt Template]\n230\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD5: Evaluator Verdict Schema]\n231\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Format Patterns — Evaluator verdict]\n232\t- [Source: src/lib/evaluator.ts#EVALUATOR_PROMPT (line 47-48)]\n233\t- [Source: src/lib/evaluator.ts#runEvaluator() — dispatchAgent call (line 128-132)]\n234\t- [Source: src/lib/agent-resolver.ts#ResolvedAgent interface (line 17-35)]\n235\t- [Source: src/lib/agent-resolver.ts#compileSubagentDefinition() (line 328-350)]\n236\t- [Source: src/schemas/agent.schema.json — agent definition schema]\n237\t- [Source: src/schemas/verdict.schema.json — verdict output schema (referenced in prompt)]\n238\t- [Source: src/lib/verdict-parser.ts — downstream consumer, not modified]\n239\t- [Source: templates/agents/evaluator.yaml — evaluator agent definition]\n240\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/6-1-evaluator-module-workspace-spawn.md — predecessor story]\n241\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/6-2-evaluator-verdict-json-schema-parsing.md — predecessor story]\n242\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WBGtD6t91yRv6Crn8gGaXn","session_id":"52ded6f4-857c-404a-a480-19bb12459ee1","uuid":"a3968d6c-210d-4daf-8a1d-1b6d0e6c1d26","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:38:37.213Z"}
