{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01UCxqTk6qe3Y22gwEZSfrHr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01R3qQxQnfmo6SPucF5617sy","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/6-3-evaluator-prompt-template-proof.md","content":"# Verification Proof: Story 6-3 — Evaluator Prompt Template\n\n**Story:** `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/6-3-evaluator-prompt-template.md`\n**Date:** 2026-04-03\n**Verification tier:** test-provable\n**Result:** ALL_PASS (10/10 ACs)\n\n---\n\n## Pre-checks\n\n### Build\n- **Command:** `npm run build`\n- **Result:** PASS — zero errors, ESM build success\n\n### Unit Tests\n- **Command:** `npm run test:unit`\n- **Result:** PASS — 4110 tests passed, 0 failed\n\n### Linter\n- **Command:** `npx eslint src/`\n- **Result:** PASS — 0 errors, 51 warnings (all pre-existing, none related to story 6-3 files)\n\n### Coverage\n- **Command:** `npx vitest run --coverage`\n- **Results for changed files:**\n  - `agent-resolver.ts`: 94.28% statements, 84.28% branches, 86.66% functions, 95.04% lines\n  - `evaluator.ts` (lib): 100% statements, 92.85% branches, 100% functions, 100% lines\n  - `evaluator.ts` (modules): 100% statements, 81.25% branches, 100% functions, 100% lines\n- All changed files exceed 80% coverage threshold.\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Verification\n\n### AC #1: evaluator.yaml contains prompt_template with required instructions\n- **Evidence:** `templates/agents/evaluator.yaml` line 22 contains `prompt_template: |` with multi-line string\n- **Content verified:** Instructions to read ACs from `./story-files/`, independently verify each AC, require evidence (commands run + output captured) for every PASS, score UNKNOWN if unable to verify, never give benefit of the doubt, re-verify from scratch\n- **Test:** `evaluator.yaml prompt_template instructs reading from ./story-files/ (AC #1, story 6-3)` — PASS\n- **Test:** `evaluator.yaml prompt_template instructs re-verification from scratch (AC #1, story 6-3)` — PASS\n- **Result:** PASS\n\n### AC #2: Anti-leniency instructions present\n- **Evidence:** `evaluator.yaml` lines 33-37 contain exact phrases:\n  - \"Assume code is broken until demonstrated otherwise\" (line 33)\n  - \"Never give benefit of the doubt\" (line 34)\n  - \"Every PASS requires commands_run evidence — if you cannot run a command to verify, score UNKNOWN\" (line 35)\n- **Test:** `evaluator.yaml prompt_template contains anti-leniency keywords (AC #2, story 6-3)` — PASS\n- **Result:** PASS\n\n### AC #3: Prompt instructs EvaluatorVerdict JSON schema output\n- **Evidence:** `evaluator.yaml` lines 58-84 contain JSON output format matching `verdict.schema.json` structure: `verdict`, `score` (passed/failed/unknown/total), `findings` array with per-AC `status`, `evidence.commands_run`, `evidence.output_observed`, `evidence.reasoning`\n- **Test:** `evaluator.yaml prompt_template references verdict JSON structure (AC #3, story 6-3)` — PASS\n- **Test:** `evaluator.yaml prompt_template instructs output to ./verdict/verdict.json (AC #3, story 6-3)` — PASS\n- **Result:** PASS\n\n### AC #4: Tool access instructions (Docker, no source code)\n- **Evidence:** `evaluator.yaml` lines 39-45: \"Docker commands: docker exec, docker logs, docker ps\", \"Observability query endpoints\", \"You do NOT have access to source code\"\n- **Test:** `evaluator.yaml prompt_template includes tool access instructions (AC #4, story 6-3)` — PASS\n- **Result:** PASS\n\n### AC #5: ResolvedAgent includes prompt_template from YAML\n- **Evidence:** `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` line 35: `prompt_template?: string` in `ResolvedAgent` interface. `resolveAgent('evaluator')` loads `evaluator.yaml` which includes `prompt_template` field.\n- **Test:** `loads evaluator.yaml with prompt_template field present (AC #5, story 6-3)` — PASS\n- **Result:** PASS\n\n### AC #6: compileSubagentDefinition incorporates prompt_template\n- **Evidence:** `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` lines 344-346: `if (agent.prompt_template) { parts.push(agent.prompt_template); }` — appends prompt_template to instructions. When absent, no change.\n- **Test:** `includes prompt_template in instructions when present (AC #6)` — PASS\n- **Test:** `output unchanged when prompt_template is absent (AC #6)` — PASS\n- **Test:** `prompt_template appears after prompt_patches.append in instructions` — PASS\n- **Result:** PASS\n\n### AC #7: evaluator.ts uses prompt template instead of hardcoded one-liner\n- **Evidence:** `src/lib/evaluator.ts` lines 55-63: `buildEvaluatorPrompt()` function replaces the old hardcoded `EVALUATOR_PROMPT` constant. The function builds a minimal dispatch prompt referencing `./story-files/` and `./verdict/verdict.json`. The full anti-leniency prompt lives in the compiled `SubagentDefinition.instructions` via prompt_template.\n- **Test:** `dispatch prompt includes story file paths reference (AC #7, story 6-3)` — PASS\n- **Test:** `dispatch prompt includes verdict output path (AC #7, story 6-3)` — PASS\n- **Test:** `compiled evaluator uses prompt_template from YAML, not a hardcoded constant` — PASS\n- **Result:** PASS\n\n### AC #8: agent.schema.json allows optional prompt_template\n- **Evidence:** `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` lines 80-83: `\"prompt_template\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"description\": \"Task-specific prompt template included in compiled instructions\" }`\n- **Test:** `accepts agent config with prompt_template (AC #8)` — PASS\n- **Test:** `accepts agent config without prompt_template (AC #8)` — PASS\n- **Test:** `rejects prompt_template with non-string type` — PASS\n- **Result:** PASS\n\n### AC #9: Unit tests pass at 80%+ coverage\n- **Evidence:** All story 6-3 tests pass (see test names above). Coverage: agent-resolver.ts 94.28% stmts, evaluator.ts (lib) 100% stmts — both exceed 80%.\n- **Tests covering story 6-3:** 20+ tests across agent-resolver.test.ts and evaluator.test.ts tagged with \"story 6-3\" or referencing AC numbers.\n- **Result:** PASS\n\n### AC #10: Build succeeds with zero errors, no test regressions\n- **Evidence:** `npm run build` exits 0 with \"Build success\". `npm run test:unit` reports 4110 passed, 0 failed.\n- **Result:** PASS\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| AC | Description | Result |\n|----|-------------|--------|\n| 1 | prompt_template in evaluator.yaml with full instructions | PASS |\n| 2 | Anti-leniency instructions present | PASS |\n| 3 | Verdict JSON schema output format | PASS |\n| 4 | Tool access instructions (Docker, no source) | PASS |\n| 5 | ResolvedAgent includes prompt_template | PASS |\n| 6 | compileSubagentDefinition incorporates prompt_template | PASS |\n| 7 | evaluator.ts uses prompt template, not hardcoded | PASS |\n| 8 | agent.schema.json allows optional prompt_template | PASS |\n| 9 | Unit tests pass at 80%+ coverage | PASS |\n| 10 | Build zero errors, no test regressions | PASS |\n\n**Final verdict: ALL_PASS (10/10 ACs)**\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":170,"cache_read_input_tokens":47246,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":170,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JbC5FbZerRqBzwGsxvEza4","session_id":"52ded6f4-857c-404a-a480-19bb12459ee1","uuid":"d34649f6-7636-441e-a23a-d1a0c40c319e"}
